# Roles and RBAC

There are four roles. Use the enum name exactly as written everywhere in code.

## CITIZEN

Regular registered user. Scoped to their own ward/municipality.

Can:

* Submit reports
* Upload photos
* Add location
* View issues in their ward and nearby
* Verify issues (CONFIRM or DISPUTE)
* Support existing reports
* View progress of issues they reported

Cannot:

* Change issue status
* Assign issues
* Access any dashboard

## LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE

Ward-level or municipality-level employee. Acts under direction of LOCAL_BODY_HEAD.
Maps to: ward secretary, palika technical officer, sanitation officer, etc.

Can:

* View issues assigned to them
* Update issue status (ASSIGNED → IN_PROGRESS → RESOLVED)
* Upload evidence/photos on updates
* Post updates to the issue timeline
* Request clarification from citizens

Cannot:

* Assign issues to other officers
* Create root issues
* View issues outside their municipality

## LOCAL_BODY_HEAD

Head of a local body (ward chairperson, municipal executive officer, etc.).
Scoped to their municipality. The primary decision-maker at local level.

Can:

* Assign issues to LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE
* Monitor all issues in their municipality
* Review and set deadlines
* View escalated issues
* Accept or reject AI root cause suggestions
* Create and manage Root Issues
* View municipality-level metrics and heatmap

Cannot:

* View issues outside their own municipality
* View national-level data

## EXECUTIVE_BODY

National-level oversight role. Ministry officials, NPC, national governance bodies.
Read-only access to everything. Cannot modify any data.

Can:

* View all issues across all municipalities and provinces
* View national heatmap of all active issues
* View system-wide transparency metrics
* Filter by province, district, municipality, category, status
* View root cause clusters nationally
* Export reports (future)

Cannot:

* Create, modify, or close any issue
* Assign any issue
* Interact with any citizen data

