# Database Rules

A Report is NOT an Issue.

Multiple Reports may belong to one Issue.

An Issue may belong to one Root Issue.

Relationships:

User → Reports
User → Verifications
User → IssueUpdates
User → AssignedIssues (as LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE)

Issue → Reports
Issue → Updates (IssueUpdate)
Issue → Verifications
Issue → AssignedTo (User, LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE)
Issue → RootIssue (optional)

RootIssue → Issues

All Issues and Reports must store: wardNumber, municipalityName, districtName, provinceName.

Issues must also store: reportCount (Int, default 1), communityImpactScore (Float, default 0.3), affectedCitizenCount (Int, default 1).

---

# Issue Status Lifecycle

Only allow these transitions. Never bypass them.

SUBMITTED → VERIFIED (3 citizen verifications OR LOCAL_BODY_HEAD manual action)
VERIFIED → ASSIGNED (LOCAL_BODY_HEAD assigns to employee)
ASSIGNED → IN_PROGRESS (LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE starts work)
IN_PROGRESS → RESOLVED (LOCAL_BODY_EMPLOYEE marks complete with evidence)
RESOLVED → REOPENED (majority of verifiers dispute resolution)
REOPENED → IN_PROGRESS (employee re-acknowledges)

---

# Escalation Rules

Computed on page load. No background jobs.

Status stuck at SUBMITTED > 48 hours → flag for LOCAL_BODY_HEAD (unverified queue)
Status stuck at VERIFIED > 72 hours → alert LOCAL_BODY_HEAD (unassigned)
Status stuck at ASSIGNED > 7 days → alert LOCAL_BODY_HEAD + employee
Status stuck at IN_PROGRESS > 14 days → critical flag (visible on EXECUTIVE_BODY dashboard too)

Priority multipliers on SLA:

* CRITICAL: 0.25x (e.g. 3.5 days for IN_PROGRESS)
* HIGH: 0.5x
* MEDIUM: 1x (default)
* LOW: 2x

Store escalatedAt on Issue when first threshold is crossed.
dueDate can be manually set by LOCAL_BODY_HEAD to override default SLA.

---

# AI Usage Rules

AI may:

* Categorize reports (category enum)
* Suggest priority (LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH / CRITICAL)
* Detect semantic duplicates (similarity score + matched issueId) — only after geospatial check finds no match
* Suggest root causes (title + reason + confidence + related issue IDs)
* Auto-elevate priority to HIGH when reportCount ≥ 8 (arithmetic, not predictive — this is the one exception to the human-approval rule)

AI must NEVER:

* Automatically resolve issues
* Automatically assign responsibility
* Automatically escalate issues
* Create any database record directly

Human validation is always required for all AI suggestions.

All AI calls use Gemini with structured JSON output. Parse and validate before storing.

